# Project Architecture

## What this project does
**Ebookarr** — a FastAPI web app that takes a Goodreads URL, finds the ebook, downloads it from LibGen via Selenium/Firefox, and sends it to a Kindle email via Gmail SMTP. Runs as `ebookarr.service` under systemd on port `19191`.

## Key files and their roles

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `service.py` | FastAPI app, `jobs` dict (module-level), all endpoints |
| `download_flow.py` | Core pipeline: `get_isbn`, `get_book_md5`, `ebook_download`, `ebook_download_by_md5`, `search_books` |
| `download_with_libgen.py` | Selenium/Firefox download from LibGen (`choose_libgen_mirror`, `get_libgen_link`, `download_book_using_selenium`) |
| `config.py` | Pydantic-settings `Settings` class — single source of truth for all config |
| `bitwarden.py` | BW CLI wrapper (currently disabled; secrets come from `.env`) |
| `static/index.html` | Alpine.js SPA — no build step, loaded from CDN |
| `tests/test_e2e.py` | Real E2E tests — no mocks, require live network + credentials |
| `books.log` | Structured log file; `@log_call` decorator logs function entry and return |
| `exceptions.py` | Custom exceptions: `BookNotFoundError`, `DownloadError`, `EmailDeliveryError`, `InvalidURLError` |

## Download pipeline status values
The `on_status` callback in `ebook_download` emits these values in order:
`queued` → `fetching_isbn` → `searching` → `downloading` → `sending` → `done`  
On failure: `error`

These values are also used in the Alpine.js `steps` array in `static/index.html`. **Both must stay in sync.**

## Tech stack
- Python runtime: `uv` (always use `uv run`, never bare `python` or `pytest`)
- Web framework: FastAPI + uvicorn
- HTML/JS: Alpine.js (CDN), no build step
- Browser automation: Selenium + Firefox (geckodriver)
- HTTP client: `aiohttp`
- HTML parsing: BeautifulSoup4
- Config: pydantic-settings + `.env`
- Tests: pytest with `e2e` marker; `uv run pytest -m e2e`

## Endpoints
- `GET /` — serves `static/index.html`
- `POST /download` — starts async download job, returns `{job_id}`
- `GET /jobs/{job_id}` — returns job status
- `GET /download/{md5}` — direct MD5 download
- `GET /search?q=...` — Goodreads book search
- `GET /health` — health check
